    "claim": "`cook()` marks `status.needsSolvencyCheck = true` after `ACTION_BORROW` and `ACTION_REMOVE_COLLATERAL`, but any later unhandled action falls through to the empty `_additionalCookAction()` implementation and blindly replaces `status` with a zero-initialized struct. Because `ACTION_ACCRUE` is declared (`8`) yet never handled in the `cook()` dispatcher, a sequence such as `[BORROW, ACCRUE]` or `[REMOVE_COLLATERAL, ACCRUE]` clears the pending solvency check and returns successfully even when `msg.sender` is insolvent.",
    "impact": "An attacker can borrow MIM without enough collateral or withdraw collateral from an already undercollateralized position, leaving immediate bad debt and draining the cauldron up to its available MIM liquidity.",
